{"questionId":"9076302","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Hubble constant is accepted to be 70 km s<sup>–1</sup> Mpc<sup>–1</sup>. This value of the Hubble constant gives an age for the universe of 14.0 billion years.</p>\n<p>The accepted value of the Hubble constant has changed over the past decades.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The redshift of a galaxy is measured to be <em>z </em>= 0.19.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate, in Mpc, the distance between the galaxy and the Earth.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>v</em> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong><em>zc</em> = 0.19&nbsp;× 3&nbsp;× 10<sup>8</sup> =<strong>»</strong> 5.7&nbsp;× 10<sup>7</sup>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>ms<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em>d</em> = <strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{v}{{{H_0}}} = \\frac{{5.7 \\times {{10}^4}}}{{70}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>H</mi>\n          <mn>0</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5.7</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>70</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> = 810Mpc &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>OR</strong></em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;8.1× 10<sup>8</sup>&nbsp;pc</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Correct units must be present for MP2 to be awarded.</em></p>\n<p><em>Award </em><strong><em>[2] </em></strong><em>for BCA.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076302","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ1.b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Estimate, in Mpc, the distance between the galaxy and the Earth.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Ma